01:24.585 --> 01:28.425
Anyway... today I went
across the street to the Apple Store,

01:28.505 --> 01:31.220
and I got one of the new iPhones
with the 64-gigabytes,

01:31.300 --> 01:34.554
'cause I wasn't sure if I should get
the 16s or the 64s,

01:34.636 --> 01:37.476
but the 64s look good, so there you go.

01:37.556 --> 01:40.521
The genius bartender showed me
how to make things bigger,

01:40.601 --> 01:41.897
but I already forgot.

01:41.977 --> 01:44.066
God, my eyesight is so shot.

01:44.146 --> 01:46.985
But I got on Google before,
and I looked up my apartment,

01:47.065 --> 01:49.818
and it said they'd filmed The Hills
there for two seasons.

01:49.901 --> 01:51.490
Isn't that neat?

01:51.570 --> 01:56.245
And they used to do the Extra program
at The Grove every day with Mario Lopez.

01:56.325 --> 01:57.996
He seems nice.

01:58.076 --> 02:00.704
And who wouldn't love an outdoor mall?

02:00.787 --> 02:04.041
I can't believe it, me in Los Angeles.

02:04.124 --> 02:06.752
If only Daddy could see me now.

02:07.961 --> 02:09.675
Today they played "Come Fly With Me,"

02:09.755 --> 02:12.008
and I almost started crying,
thinking about him.

02:12.090 --> 02:14.805
But I didn't 'cause, basically,
I feel great.

02:14.885 --> 02:17.388
It's like living on Main Street
in Disneyland.

02:17.471 --> 02:19.643
Every day is sunny,
and I wake up and I think,

02:19.723 --> 02:22.521
"Thank you, Joey, for making it possible."

02:22.601 --> 02:27.107
I swear, if I get hit by that trolley,
I'll die happy.

02:27.189 --> 02:28.657
Just wait till you see my apartment.

02:31.818 --> 02:35.117
I have a balcony that's far enough away
from other people's balconies,

02:35.197 --> 02:38.161
so nobody could jump down
from the roof or whatever.

02:38.241 --> 02:40.706
And I have a parking spot
next to the elevator,

02:40.786 --> 02:43.164
so I can just run right in there.

02:44.206 --> 02:46.378
And I got everything shipped out
from Jersey,

02:46.458 --> 02:47.835
all my artwork,

02:47.918 --> 02:50.007
the doll I had made of you,

02:50.087 --> 02:53.260
and, of course, the pictures
of me and Daddy in his red car.

02:53.340 --> 02:55.554
God, we had the best times in that thing.

02:55.634 --> 02:58.478
Anyway, call me back. Love you.

03:19.449 --> 03:21.247
Oh, God...

03:27.165 --> 03:28.211
I brought you bagels.

03:28.291 --> 03:30.380
- You should have called.
- I did.

03:30.460 --> 03:31.461
But I didn't answer.

03:31.545 --> 03:33.513
Oh, I figured you were working
or something.

03:34.631 --> 03:36.383
Say hi to your grand-dogs.

03:36.466 --> 03:39.056
Hi, doggies. How you doing?

03:39.136 --> 03:41.138
Okay. Stay there.

03:41.221 --> 03:42.893
All right, bye.

03:42.973 --> 03:45.437
Six bagels, all salt.

03:45.517 --> 03:47.314
Those are the best kind.

03:47.394 --> 03:51.149
Oh, Lor, you let Daddy's bonsai die.

03:51.231 --> 03:53.734
Oh, yeah. Sorry, Ma.

03:53.817 --> 03:57.491
I tried, but they're, like,
crazy delicate.

03:57.571 --> 03:58.743
It was crazy.

03:59.698 --> 04:00.790
Sorry, Joey.

04:01.658 --> 04:04.831
See, this is why I asked you
not to put me in charge.

04:04.911 --> 04:07.501
You can't just leave someone
with a bonsai and orchid,

04:07.581 --> 04:09.169
and put all this pressure on them.

04:09.249 --> 04:10.462
You let the orchid die, too?

04:10.542 --> 04:12.339
I watered it every day.

04:12.419 --> 04:15.008
Well, Lori, you're not supposed
to water it every day.

04:15.088 --> 04:17.302
Well, I watered it the right amount, okay?

04:17.382 --> 04:20.055
Please, don't make me
feel any more bad about it.

04:20.135 --> 04:21.557
Okay, forget it.

04:23.764 --> 04:25.983
Oh, what's this?

04:27.309 --> 04:28.647
It's Emily's baby shower.

04:28.727 --> 04:30.354
Do you get to bring somebody?

04:31.021 --> 04:32.273
Why? I probably won't go.

04:32.355 --> 04:33.568
Why not?

04:33.648 --> 04:37.903
Because I'll have to get all dressed up,
and everyone I know will be there.

04:39.780 --> 04:41.327
I thought you gave up smoking.

04:42.282 --> 04:44.329
Cigarettes. You said this was better.

04:44.409 --> 04:47.207
I said it was okay after
your father died when your stomach hurt.

04:47.287 --> 04:50.211
Well, it's after my father died,
and my stomach hurts.

04:52.751 --> 04:55.048
Well, have you heard from Jacob?

04:55.128 --> 04:56.129
You shouldn't call him.

04:57.214 --> 04:59.386
What's going on at work?
Did they call you about the pilot?

04:59.466 --> 05:01.012
You shouldn't be smoking
if you have a deadline.

05:01.092 --> 05:02.931
Mom, don't say "deadline."

05:03.011 --> 05:07.266
Don't say "pilot," and please don't ever
say the word "Jacob" again.

05:07.349 --> 05:08.976
Okay.

05:12.479 --> 05:14.526
I just think you shouldn't call him.

05:14.606 --> 05:17.530
Especially if you have a deadline
for your pilot. Jacob... I mean, I just...

05:18.610 --> 05:20.282
I think we should get you a hobby.

05:20.362 --> 05:22.160
I thought you were gonna volunteer
at the hospital.

05:22.906 --> 05:24.704
Yeah, I've been meaning to do that.

05:26.660 --> 05:28.662
Or maybe you could be my hobby?

05:32.374 --> 05:35.547
And then, you just touch the screen
like that.

05:35.627 --> 05:38.300
Look how you magnified that. That's gre...

05:38.380 --> 05:41.595
Okay, say you wanna find an address
for a baby shower.

05:41.675 --> 05:43.847
Well, then you just open Safari here,

05:43.927 --> 05:45.429
- and then you type it in.
- Or Google it.

05:45.512 --> 05:47.389
Yeah, you Google it,
and if you ever need it again,

05:47.472 --> 05:48.724
it's right there in your search history.

05:48.807 --> 05:50.979
Oh, my God. Freddy, you are a genius.

05:51.059 --> 05:52.311
It's just a label.

05:52.394 --> 05:54.396
My daughter's a genius,
but she's too old for you.

05:54.479 --> 05:57.358
- How old are you?
- I'll be 23 in October.

05:57.440 --> 06:00.864
Get out of here. October...
That makes you a Libra, right?

06:00.944 --> 06:04.619
So scales, justice...
you're probably very diplomatic.

06:05.657 --> 06:06.783
You should be a lawyer.

06:08.285 --> 06:09.411
Maybe.

06:09.494 --> 06:12.043
You should be. You should.

06:12.956 --> 06:14.208
Oh, my God.

06:14.291 --> 06:15.292
No, no, no.

06:15.375 --> 06:16.501
I'm not even a candidate for Lasik.

06:16.585 --> 06:20.383
They said they had to slice my eyeball
open and put in a little... a lens.

06:20.463 --> 06:22.302
Well, you should get what I have.
Transitions.

06:22.382 --> 06:25.386
They go from regular glasses
to sunglasses when you walk outside.

06:25.468 --> 06:27.432
And you can get them anywhere.
LensCrafters.

06:27.512 --> 06:28.764
Want me to make you an appointment?

06:28.847 --> 06:30.269
You should try Zillow.

06:31.641 --> 06:34.815
They have a lot of places to rent and...
Or just get advice.

06:34.895 --> 06:36.983
I mean, that's how I found my condo.

06:37.063 --> 06:38.276
Zillow.

06:38.356 --> 06:41.571
What you have to do is have him
tip you upside down.

06:41.651 --> 06:44.370
That's what Joe and I did
to conceive Lori.

06:44.905 --> 06:47.124
- It'll be easy. She's so petite.
- Yeah.

06:49.576 --> 06:52.415
It's another pink bunny!

06:52.495 --> 06:54.998
I love it. What's next?

06:57.500 --> 06:59.252
Is this a baby monitor?

06:59.336 --> 07:02.300
It's from Mrs. Minervini.

07:02.380 --> 07:03.802
What is it?

07:03.882 --> 07:05.930
Oh, my God.

07:07.469 --> 07:09.391
It's an iPad.

07:09.471 --> 07:10.973
What? What?

07:11.056 --> 07:13.103
- Wow. Oh, my God.
- Marnie.

07:13.183 --> 07:15.397
This is crazy generous.

07:15.477 --> 07:17.479
- Well, I know it wasn't on your list.
- No.

07:17.562 --> 07:19.526
But, I was in the Apple store
the other day

07:19.606 --> 07:22.696
and I saw this little Filipino boy,
practically a baby,

07:22.776 --> 07:24.403
and he was playing with one of these...

07:24.486 --> 07:26.157
- I mean, what do you...
- iPad.

07:26.237 --> 07:28.201
iPad, yes. And then Freddy came over,

07:28.281 --> 07:31.000
and he told me
that you can load in programs...

07:31.952 --> 07:35.417
like Nemo and Barney's Circus...

07:35.497 --> 07:36.710
- Brilliant.
- Yes.

07:36.790 --> 07:40.088
Brilliant. Marnie, thank you.
This is so nice.

07:40.168 --> 07:42.215
Lori has the best mum ever.

07:42.295 --> 07:45.299
Apart from my mum. Did you get that down?

07:45.382 --> 07:46.759
- I'm gonna write it down.
- Write it down. Yeah.

07:46.841 --> 07:49.014
Hey, where is Lori?

07:49.094 --> 07:52.642
I think she's working. She had a deadline.

07:52.722 --> 07:54.060
I mean, a countdown.

07:54.140 --> 07:57.144
Yeah, she said
she'd watch Tehya for me tonight.

07:57.227 --> 07:59.355
Dani and I haven't been able to get
out in, like, a year.

07:59.437 --> 08:01.902
- Oh, I could do it.
- I thought she was out of town.

08:01.982 --> 08:03.403
She told me she was sick.

08:03.483 --> 08:05.155
Well, she was sick. She was.

08:05.235 --> 08:08.199
I'd be sick too with everything
Jacob puts her through.

08:08.279 --> 08:11.119
She's so pretty.
Why can't she just get over him?

08:11.199 --> 08:13.496
Well, he was the last person
to meet her dad.

08:13.576 --> 08:15.078
Oh, yeah, he really loved her dad.

08:15.161 --> 08:16.162
That's tough to get over.

08:16.246 --> 08:19.669
She's not gonna get over him
if she keeps giving him what he wants.

08:19.749 --> 08:20.750
What does he want?

08:20.834 --> 08:23.838
Oh, my God!

08:24.879 --> 08:26.217
I'm dying.

08:26.297 --> 08:28.261
What does he want?

08:28.341 --> 08:29.888
It wasn't on the list either.

08:32.011 --> 08:33.308
Marnie? Marnie?

08:33.388 --> 08:35.390
This is Greg's dad.

08:35.472 --> 08:37.562
He came out to help us with the nursery.

08:37.642 --> 08:39.736
- Marnie.
- Hi. Mark.

08:40.477 --> 08:43.277
- He's in town till Thursday, so...
- Yeah.

08:46.401 --> 08:48.074
She's a character, huh?

08:49.237 --> 08:50.238
Well...

08:50.321 --> 08:53.286
So you came out, to see your son?

08:53.366 --> 08:56.119
Yeah, Emily said it was
very important that I come,

08:56.202 --> 08:58.421
but I think I'm just here to carry gifts.

08:59.956 --> 09:02.754
Yeah. Well, his mother's
not around anymore, so...

09:02.834 --> 09:04.798
My husband died a year ago.

09:04.878 --> 09:06.675
Oh, she's alive. She lives in London.

09:06.755 --> 09:08.093
But, you know, we're divorced.

09:08.173 --> 09:09.174
Oh, sorry.

09:11.718 --> 09:13.765
Emily tells me you grew up in Brooklyn?

09:13.845 --> 09:15.472
- Yeah.
- Which... which part?

09:15.555 --> 09:17.478
Sunset Park.

09:18.892 --> 09:22.816
I grew up on the corner of 48th
and 7th Avenue, right by the church.

09:22.896 --> 09:24.567
- Get outta here.
- Yeah.

09:24.647 --> 09:28.571
I grew up at 43rd and 4th,
by the other church.

09:28.651 --> 09:31.950
Yeah. We used to go to the public pool
there, before it became a parking lot.

09:32.030 --> 09:34.533
Get out of here,
I went there all the time!

09:35.241 --> 09:37.539
I'll bet we moved in similar circles.

09:37.619 --> 09:40.709
Oh, absolutely. That's crazy.

09:40.789 --> 09:42.502
- Yeah, yeah.
- That's funny.

09:42.582 --> 09:45.085
Hey, you know, before I leave town,

09:45.168 --> 09:48.258
we should go have lunch, you know,
with the girls.

09:48.338 --> 09:53.138
Or, there's this holocaust museum
I've been really wanting to check out.

09:53.218 --> 09:54.970
Have you been to the holocaust museum?

09:55.053 --> 09:58.143
No. It sounds like fun, but I can't.

09:58.223 --> 10:00.562
I really can't
because I've just moved in, you know.

10:00.642 --> 10:03.815
I've got all my paperwork I gotta do,
and, you know...

10:03.895 --> 10:06.317
Plus, I'm volunteering at the hospital,

10:06.397 --> 10:08.194
and I might also be babysitting.

10:08.274 --> 10:11.614
I'm not sure, but it looks
like pretty soon I might be babysitting.

10:11.694 --> 10:14.243
But I've never been so busy.

10:16.741 --> 10:18.118
Okay, so I'm just calling

10:18.201 --> 10:21.416
to tell you that I'm on my way
to the hospital to volunteer.

10:21.496 --> 10:24.210
And so, call me back and, soon,

10:24.290 --> 10:26.838
because once I get in there, then,
I mean, I'll be in there

10:26.918 --> 10:28.795
and you won't be able to reach me. So...

10:28.878 --> 10:31.718
Oh, and did I tell you
about this new BeyoncÃ© song?

10:31.798 --> 10:33.015
Listen to this.

10:36.511 --> 10:39.139
Yeah? Right? So, anyway, yeah.

10:39.222 --> 10:41.475
So call me soon
because once I get in there,

10:41.558 --> 10:43.897
then you won't be able to reach me. Okay.

10:43.977 --> 10:46.275
So, bye. Call me.

11:04.414 --> 11:07.293
...discovered in the Angeles
National Forest within ten miles

11:07.375 --> 11:09.547
of where the skeletal remains were found.

11:09.627 --> 11:13.051
Police suspect this could be the work
of a serial killer that's been targeting

11:13.131 --> 11:15.720
young women in the area since 2005.

11:15.800 --> 11:17.802
Well, we've got dangerous riptides
in Malibu.

11:17.886 --> 11:20.183
What do you need to know if you're
headed to the beach this weekend?

11:20.263 --> 11:22.265
Well, it may be sunny...

11:23.308 --> 11:25.105
Lor?

11:25.185 --> 11:26.812
Lori?

11:26.895 --> 11:29.523
Don't you bring your mail in anymore?

11:29.606 --> 11:31.529
Lor.

11:33.526 --> 11:34.698
Lori?

11:36.988 --> 11:39.241
You're not bringing the mail in?

11:40.116 --> 11:41.117
Jesus.

11:41.201 --> 11:43.998
Mom! You have to ring the doorbell.

11:44.078 --> 11:45.166
But I've got the key.

11:45.246 --> 11:46.793
Well, what if I had company?

11:46.873 --> 11:48.716
You mean like Jacob?

11:49.417 --> 11:50.505
Who told you that?

11:50.585 --> 11:52.053
Your friends at the baby shower.

11:54.255 --> 11:57.679
Mom, please don't talk to my friends,
okay?

11:57.759 --> 12:01.975
And you're not supposed to go as a
"plus one" if there isn't a one to plus.

12:02.055 --> 12:04.769
But you never told me
if you were going or not.

12:04.849 --> 12:07.814
Oh, did you get my message
about the serial killer?

12:07.894 --> 12:11.568
The guy that's going all around Southern
California targeting young women?

12:11.648 --> 12:13.901
Well, we should be fine, then.

12:13.983 --> 12:16.906
Well, I was thinking that we should
get a system in place where

12:16.986 --> 12:19.534
every time you're leaving the house,
you call me,

12:19.614 --> 12:22.078
and then you text me when you're home.

12:22.158 --> 12:23.997
That's crazy.

12:24.077 --> 12:27.625
Well, I just mean until, you know,
until they catch the guy.

12:27.705 --> 12:30.503
And if you run into him,
you know what you're supposed to do.

12:30.583 --> 12:34.053
It's, like, eyes, throat, crotch.

12:34.587 --> 12:35.964
Crotch.

12:36.047 --> 12:40.013
Mom, maybe you shouldn't drop
around here all the time.

12:40.093 --> 12:42.187
But I barely see you anymore.

12:43.346 --> 12:47.852
Well, you know,
I've got a ton of work to do, so...

12:47.934 --> 12:51.484
you know, it requires a lot of research.

12:52.522 --> 12:54.194
I'm just saying,

12:54.274 --> 12:58.198
I'm not in the position
to be very entertaining right now.

12:58.278 --> 13:00.030
I don't have any good stories.

13:00.113 --> 13:01.786
Is there anything you wanna talk about?

13:03.408 --> 13:06.582
Didn't you hear what I just said?

13:07.954 --> 13:10.668
What I need right now is to write.

13:10.748 --> 13:11.920
Okay?

13:12.000 --> 13:14.464
This is my office.

13:14.544 --> 13:15.590
This is my desk.

13:15.670 --> 13:17.759
These are my co-workers.

13:17.839 --> 13:22.305
If I was in a real office,
you wouldn't come in and sit on my desk,

13:22.385 --> 13:24.349
and pet my co-workers, would you?

13:24.429 --> 13:26.056
No?

13:30.059 --> 13:34.275
I've been talking to my therapist
about this, and...

13:34.355 --> 13:39.828
I think it's time that we...
set some boundaries.

13:41.446 --> 13:42.948
Sure.

13:43.031 --> 13:44.533
Yep.

13:44.615 --> 13:46.413
I get it.

13:47.243 --> 13:48.831
You need to write...

13:48.911 --> 13:51.125
and I need to...

13:51.205 --> 13:53.128
get out of your office.

13:55.126 --> 13:56.878
But you don't have to leave right now.

13:56.961 --> 14:01.137
No, it's fine. It's fine. I don't want
to be crossing anybody's boundaries.

14:04.469 --> 14:07.934
I don't know.
She seems so angry all the time.

14:08.014 --> 14:11.484
You've been seeing her for a while.
Has she always seemed so angry?

14:16.522 --> 14:18.194
And I just, I don't...

14:18.274 --> 14:20.947
I don't want her to hurt herself
or anything.

14:21.027 --> 14:22.615
I mean, does she talk to you about that?

14:22.695 --> 14:24.742
I'm not saying that I want to know
what she says.

14:24.822 --> 14:26.950
I'm just saying that
if she talks to you about stuff,

14:27.033 --> 14:28.454
I hope she talks to you about that stuff,

14:28.534 --> 14:30.081
and that you talk to her about that stuff,

14:30.161 --> 14:33.459
and that you make sure
she doesn't hurt herself or anything.

14:33.539 --> 14:37.669
And, you know, maybe also tell her
to stop smoking so much grass.

14:37.752 --> 14:42.927
I know she's in...
some stage of grief or something, but...

14:43.007 --> 14:45.930
- And what about you?
- What about me?

14:46.010 --> 14:47.011
How do you feel?

14:47.095 --> 14:50.893
Well, I feel she should find some other
way to feel better besides marijuana.

14:50.973 --> 14:54.568
No, I mean how do you feel
since your husband died?

15:00.066 --> 15:03.696
Well, of course I feel sad.

15:06.864 --> 15:08.536
But I don't think I'm as stressed as Lori,

15:08.616 --> 15:11.414
because I don't have to worry
about my career or money.

15:11.494 --> 15:13.872
Because Joey, God bless him,
he set me up for life.

15:13.955 --> 15:15.582
So I can do...

15:15.665 --> 15:17.042
I can do anything.

15:17.125 --> 15:20.755
I mean, like, when I go
to an action movie, I get three tickets,

15:20.837 --> 15:23.551
one for me, one for Joe,
one for my mother.

15:23.631 --> 15:26.305
And I don't even have to think about it.
I don't have to worry about it.

15:30.680 --> 15:32.226
I spend...

15:32.306 --> 15:33.933
a lot of time by myself.

15:34.892 --> 15:37.896
And, well, there are a lot of hours
in the day

15:37.979 --> 15:41.779
and so sometimes I don't know what to do
with them, and I call Lori...

15:42.525 --> 15:44.072
but she...

15:44.152 --> 15:45.529
Well, she doesn't...

15:45.611 --> 15:47.408
She doesn't want my advice or anything.

15:47.488 --> 15:49.115
I mean, I have nothing...

15:50.241 --> 15:52.164
important to say.

15:55.746 --> 15:58.336
But basically, I feel great.

15:58.416 --> 16:00.669
I love my apartment.

16:01.419 --> 16:03.007
You can't beat this weather.

16:03.087 --> 16:04.675
And who doesn't love The Grove?

16:04.755 --> 16:07.383
I mean, it's like living on Main Street
in Disneyland.

16:38.623 --> 16:41.671
Anyway, call me and let me
know you got in safe.

16:41.751 --> 16:43.970
Oh, and remind me to tell you
what your therapist said.

16:47.548 --> 16:51.347
...very little information about the
message left behind by the serial killer

16:51.427 --> 16:53.555
who is asking to be called
the "Red Ripper."

17:34.554 --> 17:37.977
It's so good to see you out of the house,

17:38.057 --> 17:40.230
and on such a nice occasion.

