17:53.573 --> 17:56.245
So, listen, Mom,

17:56.325 --> 17:59.165
I have to go to New York for a few weeks
to shoot the pilot.

17:59.245 --> 18:01.042
New York? Why?

18:01.122 --> 18:03.961
Well, 'cause the show is set there,
so it's, it's actually good,

18:04.041 --> 18:07.882
but I'm not gonna be reachable
for a few weeks,

18:07.962 --> 18:09.050
like, at all.

18:09.130 --> 18:12.259
Like, somebody else is gonna be
holding my phone for me.

18:12.341 --> 18:15.014
But I was thinking at the end

18:15.094 --> 18:17.266
if you wanted to come and visit the set

18:17.346 --> 18:21.145
and we could finally think about

18:21.225 --> 18:23.189
getting a headstone for Dad,

18:23.269 --> 18:26.148
or, you know, at least figure out
what to do with his ashes.

18:26.230 --> 18:28.194
Yeah, well, we don't have to talk
about it now.

18:28.274 --> 18:30.738
We can wait until, you know,
before you go and then...

18:30.818 --> 18:32.615
I leave tomorrow.

18:32.695 --> 18:34.038
Tomorrow?

18:35.906 --> 18:37.245
That's really soon.

18:37.325 --> 18:41.330
I know. But maybe you could come over
tonight and help me pack,

18:41.412 --> 18:44.416
and maybe even crash so you could
give me a ride to the airport tomorrow?

18:44.498 --> 18:46.963
- That'd be fun.
- How about if I go with you?

18:47.043 --> 18:49.922
If I go with you,
I could be like your assistant.

18:50.004 --> 18:51.842
No, no.

18:51.922 --> 18:54.512
I think, if anything, I'd need you here,

18:54.592 --> 18:58.768
you know, to watch the house
and look after your grand-dogs.

19:01.724 --> 19:03.317
It's my job, Mom.

19:04.977 --> 19:06.691
Yeah, yeah. Sure, you're right.

19:06.771 --> 19:08.523
You're right. It's great.
It's a good idea.

19:09.732 --> 19:10.733
It's a good opportunity.

19:10.816 --> 19:11.988
- It is, you know.
- It's good.

19:12.068 --> 19:14.407
And it's really good timing for me,
you know?

19:14.487 --> 19:18.786
I can get out of town and be busy,
and finally take my mind off things.

19:18.866 --> 19:20.994
- Jacob!
- Exactly.

19:25.122 --> 19:27.169
Excuse me, can I get a picture with you?

19:27.249 --> 19:28.501
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

19:29.251 --> 19:31.173
Thank you so much.

19:31.253 --> 19:33.756
Hey, you two.

19:33.839 --> 19:35.261
Hey, you two!

19:35.341 --> 19:37.179
- Hi.
- Hey, Marnie.

19:37.259 --> 19:40.559
Jacob, it's good to see you. You know,
I never said anything bad about you.

19:42.056 --> 19:44.353
- You know, Elise, right?
- Yes.

19:44.433 --> 19:46.401
- Yeah.
- How are you doing?

19:47.520 --> 19:50.067
Well, we don't want to interrupt your,
your girl time.

19:50.147 --> 19:52.194
No! No, no, it's fine.

19:52.274 --> 19:55.448
We're just doing a drive-by
until I go out later.

19:55.528 --> 19:58.782
I didn't want her to have to spend
Valentine's Day alone.

19:58.864 --> 20:00.741
I didn't want her to spend it alone,
either.

20:00.825 --> 20:03.039
- I'm not alone.
- No. We're together.

20:03.119 --> 20:04.665
Until later,
when I'm meeting other people.

20:04.745 --> 20:07.543
- I thought we were having a sleepover?
- No.

20:07.623 --> 20:10.593
That's so cute!
I wish my mom and I were that close.

20:11.669 --> 20:14.047
Well, maybe, when you get older.

20:19.427 --> 20:20.804
What would make you happy?

20:20.886 --> 20:24.140
If I could be stuffed into a cannon
and shot into outer space.

20:24.223 --> 20:25.816
Should we go get milkshakes?

20:26.809 --> 20:28.856
I'm going to kill myself.

20:28.936 --> 20:30.900
- Don't say that.
- I can't live here anymore.

20:30.980 --> 20:32.357
There's no safe place.

20:32.440 --> 20:35.529
I mean, just when I want to hit
the eject button, you move here.

20:35.609 --> 20:36.697
What does that mean?

20:36.777 --> 20:39.405
It means that I tried to book a session
with my therapist

20:39.488 --> 20:43.118
to talk about my mother and I couldn't
because my mother was there!

20:43.200 --> 20:45.915
You told me to go talk to her
after Daddy died, so...

20:45.995 --> 20:47.458
Do you understand?

20:47.538 --> 20:50.667
Eighty percent of the time
the phone rings, it's you!

20:50.750 --> 20:55.091
The phone rings and I think it
could be a job, or a guy, or a friend,

20:55.171 --> 20:58.969
and it's my mother!
Almost every single time.

20:59.049 --> 21:02.178
Do you understand how terrible
that makes me feel?

21:03.554 --> 21:05.267
I can call less.

21:05.347 --> 21:06.769
I can. I can just...

21:06.849 --> 21:09.443
Well, like if you don't get back to me,
I'll just text.

21:13.355 --> 21:15.277
I'm never gonna get over him.

21:15.357 --> 21:16.734
How can I help? What can I do?

21:16.817 --> 21:18.364
Nothing.

21:18.444 --> 21:20.866
Well, then who are you texting?
Don't act out.

21:20.946 --> 21:23.825
I need to have sex with someone else,
and you can't be here for it.

21:23.908 --> 21:25.910
Okay, but just not Jacob.

21:25.993 --> 21:29.998
Please, Mom, I can't do this anymore.
I need to get a life of my own, okay?

21:30.080 --> 21:31.297
And so do you!

21:36.212 --> 21:38.681
I still need a ride to the airport.

21:44.345 --> 21:45.766
You have everything?

21:45.846 --> 21:47.348
I have no idea.

21:49.892 --> 21:52.982
Passengers only. No parking.

21:53.062 --> 21:55.110
- Love you.
- Love you.

22:30.599 --> 22:34.069
Blue team to ICU, please. Blue team, ICU.

22:49.618 --> 22:53.168
Hi. Hello.

22:55.708 --> 23:00.007
You all by yourself,
because your thing's beeping.

23:00.087 --> 23:02.556
There's nobody with you?

23:04.675 --> 23:07.598
I think, maybe, you got tangled.

23:07.678 --> 23:09.055
Let me look.

23:09.138 --> 23:10.890
I don't know.

23:11.724 --> 23:13.601
The wires or something here?

23:15.394 --> 23:18.273
There you go. See? Is that better?

23:18.355 --> 23:19.857
You seem like you...

23:20.941 --> 23:25.071
Okay. Well, I'll go get somebody
that knows what they're doing.

23:25.821 --> 23:30.418
You can keep the little bunny.
He likes it there.

23:31.911 --> 23:34.460
The woman in 317, she's in pain.

23:41.629 --> 23:43.843
Marnie, hi! What are you doing here?

23:43.923 --> 23:45.925
You said you needed a babysitter.

23:46.008 --> 23:47.429
I brought bagels.

23:47.509 --> 23:49.887
Oh, come in, please.

23:50.930 --> 23:52.273
All salt.

23:54.516 --> 23:57.690
You know what nobody ever tells you
is how lonely it is.

23:57.770 --> 24:00.398
I swear, I feel like there are some days

24:00.481 --> 24:03.985
where I go an entire day
without seeing another grown person.

24:04.068 --> 24:08.242
Like, by the time Dani gets home I don't
even know how to shut off the baby-talk.

24:08.322 --> 24:09.994
That is so normal.

24:10.074 --> 24:11.662
- Really?
- Really.

24:11.742 --> 24:14.164
But, you know, you have to remember
that she's gonna grow up.

24:14.244 --> 24:16.667
She's not gonna stay a little kid forever.

24:16.747 --> 24:18.711
And then you'll be having
real conversations.

24:18.791 --> 24:21.010
You'll talk about everything,
the way me and Lori do.

24:22.169 --> 24:24.341
Yeah, I know. Well, you're right, I know.

24:24.421 --> 24:28.301
God, I don't know why I'm so worried
about, like, doing it right.

24:28.384 --> 24:31.137
I... I lost my mom when I was young,

24:31.220 --> 24:34.268
so I'm... I'm flying blind.

24:34.348 --> 24:36.726
Lori told me something about that.
I'm sorry.

24:37.810 --> 24:40.563
But you can call me anytime to babysit
if you want.

24:41.480 --> 24:46.071
God, Lori is so lucky to have you
so close if she ever has kids.

24:46.151 --> 24:48.574
My dad couldn't even fly in
for my fake wedding.

24:48.654 --> 24:50.907
You know, I had to walk myself
down the aisle.

24:51.740 --> 24:53.329
Why was your wedding fake?

24:53.409 --> 24:56.413
Oh, because, yeah, it was at city hall.

24:56.495 --> 24:59.248
And, like, we'd just found out
the adoption was going through.

24:59.331 --> 25:02.922
And so, you know, I convinced myself
I just wanted a quickie wedding,

25:03.002 --> 25:05.255
and then I thought we'd have
a real wedding once Tehya came home,

25:05.337 --> 25:09.511
but now it just...
It feels selfish to spend any money

25:09.591 --> 25:12.556
I'd spend on her on, like,
giving us a special day, so...

25:12.636 --> 25:15.014
But what about Dani, is he working?

25:15.097 --> 25:17.394
Oh, she. Yeah, she's a chef at Bouchon,

25:17.474 --> 25:21.104
but she's, like, fifth in line
and works crazy hours.

25:21.186 --> 25:23.814
She does.

25:28.235 --> 25:30.074
What if I gave you the money?

25:30.154 --> 25:31.531
- What?
- Yeah.

25:31.613 --> 25:34.366
You know, I can gift a certain amount
of money every year to a person

25:34.450 --> 25:36.997
without having to pay taxes, and I...

25:37.077 --> 25:40.581
I don't know if it's gonna be enough
for your dream wedding, but $13,000...

25:40.664 --> 25:43.629
- Marnie, that's crazy.
- No. What's crazy?

25:43.709 --> 25:47.049
I have it, you need it. I mean, you just
don't want to leave it sitting around.

25:47.129 --> 25:50.302
Well, no. You should save it.
Spend it on yourself.

25:50.382 --> 25:53.010
I mean, wouldn't Lori be upset?

25:53.093 --> 25:55.057
Why? She's not getting married.

25:55.137 --> 25:57.481
Why would you even want to do that?

25:58.307 --> 26:02.733
It's romantic and, you know,
renewing your vows.

26:03.854 --> 26:05.731
Joe and I talked about that.

26:07.483 --> 26:09.110
Who doesn't love love?

26:10.277 --> 26:12.029
Oh, my God! Marnie!

26:12.112 --> 26:13.283
This is amazing!

26:13.363 --> 26:16.328
I mean, well, obviously, you're gonna be
involved in all of the planning.

26:16.408 --> 26:18.080
Only whatever you want me to be part of.

26:18.160 --> 26:20.582
- What do you think you want?
- Oh, my God.

26:20.662 --> 26:22.501
Nothing, like, extravagant.

26:22.581 --> 26:26.130
Dani was in the navy,
so maybe like a nautical theme.

26:26.210 --> 26:29.133
You could wear a little sailor dress
and he... she could wear her uniform.

26:29.213 --> 26:31.966
And it would be like
Officer and a Gentleman.

26:34.343 --> 26:36.890
Or you could do it on a submarine.

26:36.970 --> 26:39.223
Well, I don't see any submarines for rent,

26:39.306 --> 26:41.979
but there are a bunch of boats
at the Yacht Club in Marina Del Rey.

26:42.059 --> 26:43.731
That you can rent for a party?

26:43.811 --> 26:45.733
Yeah, looks like it.

26:45.813 --> 26:47.611
Freddy, you are a genius.

26:49.108 --> 26:52.863
Oh, jeez. It's $10,000 just for the venue.

26:54.113 --> 26:55.114
Look at that.

26:55.197 --> 26:57.450
I should get one of these for my daughter.

26:57.533 --> 27:00.036
Here, why don't you ring me up
another iPad?

27:00.119 --> 27:02.121
Yeah, sure.

27:03.747 --> 27:06.920
You know, I decided to take your advice.

27:07.000 --> 27:08.714
You're gonna be a lawyer?

27:08.794 --> 27:10.966
Well, no. But I am going to school.

27:11.046 --> 27:12.342
I mean, it's night school,

27:12.422 --> 27:15.676
but maybe engineering or programming,
or something.

27:15.759 --> 27:17.056
See how far I can get.

27:17.136 --> 27:19.224
And work's gonna pay for it, so...

27:19.304 --> 27:21.769
Oh, Freddy, you took my advice.

27:21.849 --> 27:26.229
Yeah, now all I have to do is figure out
my work schedule and the bus schedule.

27:26.311 --> 27:27.563
You don't have a car?

27:27.646 --> 27:30.819
Nah, my mom uses it for work, but it's
okay. I don't mind taking a bus.

27:30.899 --> 27:32.571
Meet a lot of freaky people on there.

27:32.651 --> 27:34.239
No, I could drive you. When?

27:34.319 --> 27:35.365
What are you talking about?

27:35.445 --> 27:37.948
I'm in the neighborhood, you're always
helping me out all the time.

27:38.031 --> 27:40.784
This will be my chance to pay you back.

27:40.868 --> 27:42.996
Oh, my God.
Do we have to take the freeway?

27:43.078 --> 27:45.501
I mean, we could avoid it,
but are you sure?

27:45.581 --> 27:47.294
- I mean, it's kind of late.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

27:47.374 --> 27:49.838
No, no, I... Don't worry about it.

27:49.918 --> 27:52.592
I don't sleep much.

28:33.420 --> 28:34.922
What?

28:35.923 --> 28:37.925
Cut! Cut!

28:38.008 --> 28:40.222
Hey, are you...
Are you supposed to be here?

28:40.302 --> 28:42.020
Here? Okay.

28:42.763 --> 28:45.602
Background, cross over,
talk to the woman in the blue hat.

28:45.682 --> 28:47.354
Okay?

28:47.434 --> 28:50.028
Yeah, killing the flowers.
Take that from you.

28:50.979 --> 28:52.981
Okay, losing the sweater.

28:53.065 --> 28:54.157
Losing the sweater.

28:55.234 --> 28:57.781
- Sorry about that.
- Take your time, Chance.

28:57.861 --> 28:59.324
Okay. Great.

28:59.404 --> 29:02.369
Great. All right!

29:02.449 --> 29:03.826
We're gonna go again!

29:05.869 --> 29:06.995
Mark.

29:07.871 --> 29:09.498
All right, background!

29:11.208 --> 29:13.711
Action!

29:13.794 --> 29:15.171
Hi.

29:15.254 --> 29:16.722
Anyways, I was just walking...

29:17.756 --> 29:19.554
So, we do it this way...

29:27.307 --> 29:28.308
Cut!

29:28.392 --> 29:30.105
- Anyway...
- Background!

29:30.185 --> 29:33.358
...the craziest thing happened.
You would not believe.

29:33.438 --> 29:37.362
I wandered onto a Hollywood movie set
and ended up being a part of the action.

29:37.442 --> 29:39.531
Isn't that wild?

29:39.611 --> 29:44.082
They say movie stars aren't nice people,
but they really are.

29:50.205 --> 29:51.957
Half-day today?

29:55.085 --> 29:58.675
I don't think I'll go back,
but I'm glad I did it.

29:58.755 --> 30:02.259
Then three nights a week I take Freddy
to his class and we talk the whole way.

30:02.342 --> 30:04.219
And they're alive when he scalps them.

30:04.303 --> 30:07.017
- No way.
- And then, he eats their brains.

30:07.097 --> 30:09.561
Oh, no! That's sick!

30:09.641 --> 30:10.687
- I know.
- That's sick!

30:10.767 --> 30:11.813
I know. I know.

30:11.893 --> 30:13.520
- Three, two, one.
- And I've been having a great time

30:13.603 --> 30:15.192
doing wedding plans with what's-her-name.

30:15.272 --> 30:16.273
Oh, my God!

30:18.066 --> 30:21.240
She seems really excited
and loves all my ideas.

30:21.320 --> 30:25.450
And I know who the flower girl is.

30:25.532 --> 30:26.703
Oh, I wonder who?

30:26.783 --> 30:29.373
And I've been really getting
into volunteering at the hospital.

30:29.453 --> 30:31.956
You should come down here with me
sometime and meet the staff.

30:32.039 --> 30:34.167
And not married. That's so funny.

30:34.249 --> 30:36.296
My daughter's not married, either.

30:36.376 --> 30:40.092
Anyway, I just wanted you to know that
I'm keeping busy with all my stuff

30:40.172 --> 30:41.969
and, basically, I feel great.

30:42.049 --> 30:45.472
So, give me a call and, let me
know you're safe and sound.

30:45.552 --> 30:48.267
And I hope you're not thinking
about Jacob too much.

30:48.347 --> 30:50.600
Love you... Hello, is...

30:51.558 --> 30:55.023
- Is that you? Hello?
- Marnie, is that you?

30:55.103 --> 30:56.195
It's Tony.

30:56.980 --> 31:00.445
I'm here with Cos and Dominic
and we all wanted to say hi.

31:00.525 --> 31:03.153
- Here, talk to Dom.
- Hey, Marnie, how are you?

31:03.236 --> 31:04.738
Hey, Dom. How are you feeling?

31:04.821 --> 31:07.035
Are you coming back to Jersey
for Joe's anniversary?

31:07.115 --> 31:10.789
Yeah, sure, but maybe not
actually on the actual day.

31:10.869 --> 31:15.124
I have to get settled first and then
as soon as I feel a bit more settled

31:15.207 --> 31:17.796
then I'm gonna come and, you know,
I'll book a flight

31:17.876 --> 31:20.048
and then I'll come see you guys.

31:20.128 --> 31:21.380
How's Ange? How's she doing?

31:21.463 --> 31:23.552
She's good, she's good.
Yeah, you want to talk to her? Angie!

31:23.632 --> 31:25.345
No, if she's busy, it's okay.

31:25.425 --> 31:27.764
- Don't...
- Marnie, where are you?

31:27.844 --> 31:29.308
When are you coming to visit?

31:29.388 --> 31:30.809
Soon. I just...

31:30.889 --> 31:33.562
Right now I just have
an awful lot on my plate, so...

31:33.642 --> 31:37.190
Have you thought about what kind
of a headstone you want to get for Joe?

31:37.270 --> 31:41.150
We were talking and Tony thought
it should have a quote on it.

31:43.902 --> 31:47.075
Just... I'm really busy right now,
you know.

31:47.155 --> 31:48.994
I'm planning a wedding
and I'm dog-sitting.

31:49.074 --> 31:51.413
And then, then I have this friend
that I'm driving places.

31:51.493 --> 31:52.745
And so it's, it's...

31:52.828 --> 31:55.167
You know, I really got a lot going...

31:55.247 --> 31:57.544
Oh, shoot, Ange, I just...

31:57.624 --> 32:01.504
There's a problem I got to fix,
so, you know, can I call you back?

32:01.586 --> 32:03.213
I'll call you back, okay. Bye.

32:13.515 --> 32:16.394
You don't have to say anything
if you don't want to.

32:18.103 --> 32:20.356
Is it something that happened at work?

32:20.439 --> 32:22.316
He just always does this to me.

32:22.399 --> 32:24.946
- Your boss?
- No. No, my brother.

32:25.026 --> 32:27.616
He sends this e-mail saying
he wants to see me.

32:27.696 --> 32:30.243
I'm not even talking to him,
but he's still telling me what to do.

32:30.323 --> 32:31.620
Why aren't you talking to him?

32:31.700 --> 32:32.996
He's always getting me in trouble.

32:33.076 --> 32:35.123
It's the same thing since we were kids.

32:35.203 --> 32:38.753
As soon as I get something good going,
he goes and just tries to wreck it.

32:43.420 --> 32:47.300
You know, Freddy, sometimes a person
seems like they don't really care,

32:47.382 --> 32:51.012
but really they're just
not as strong as you are.

32:51.094 --> 32:56.521
I bet your mother would be really happy
if you gave him another chance.

33:00.812 --> 33:02.689
Anyway, thanks.

33:07.652 --> 33:10.121
Be extraordinary!

33:11.448 --> 33:14.201
I just... I will wear anything,
but I do not look good in strapless.

33:14.284 --> 33:18.164
No. I mean, I don't look good
in anything, so I don't know.

33:18.246 --> 33:20.544
That's crazy. But everybody
looks good in a wrap dress.

33:20.624 --> 33:23.463
Excuse me, how many bridesmaids are there?

33:23.543 --> 33:27.467
Oh, well, there's me,
Emily, Trish, Stacy, Casey.

33:27.547 --> 33:31.138
- Wow.
- Katie M., Katie P., Molly,

33:31.218 --> 33:34.182
- Gina, Amy, Fern...
- Fern.

33:34.262 --> 33:36.101
Oh, and Wendy.

33:36.181 --> 33:37.853
Who am I forgetting?

33:37.933 --> 33:40.647
Oh, Lori. If she's even in town.

33:40.727 --> 33:42.065
- Oh, she'll be there.
- Are you sure?

33:42.145 --> 33:44.943
'Cause the dresses are color-coordinated
and we need an odd number.

33:45.023 --> 33:46.775
She'll be there. I'll make sure.

33:46.858 --> 33:49.111
- Okay.
- Did you really book Blues Traveler?

33:49.194 --> 33:52.198
The guy with the harmonica? Yeah.
He's fantastic.

33:52.280 --> 33:54.157
- Very cool.
- Yeah, really cool.

33:54.241 --> 33:55.242
Okay, you guys...

33:57.536 --> 33:59.163
- That's it.
- It's really white.

33:59.246 --> 34:00.917
This is the one.

34:00.997 --> 34:02.499
I could murder you.

34:02.582 --> 34:03.708
- Oh, my God.
- Oh, my God.

34:03.792 --> 34:06.921
- You look so skinny.
- Okay.

34:07.003 --> 34:09.505
Well, no, don't fall so in love yet,
because I'm actually,

34:09.589 --> 34:11.091
I'm not gonna get this exact dress,

34:11.174 --> 34:12.551
but I am gonna copy the design

34:12.634 --> 34:15.012
and buy cheaper fabric,
and then have it made at half the price.

34:15.094 --> 34:16.391
Oh, Jesus.

34:16.471 --> 34:19.520
You look so beautiful.

34:20.516 --> 34:22.731
- I'm so happy for her.
- Are you okay?

34:22.811 --> 34:25.313
- Don't do this.
- She's so skinny. She looks fantastic.

34:25.397 --> 34:26.485
- Don't do that.
- Happy for her?

34:26.565 --> 34:28.904
- No, I'm really happy for her.
- Do you really love it?

34:28.984 --> 34:31.987
Oh, Marnie, of course, but, you know...

34:32.070 --> 34:33.617
She looks great. She looks really lovely.

34:34.155 --> 34:35.281
- What...
- No!

34:35.364 --> 34:37.078
What did... No! What did you do?

34:37.158 --> 34:40.036
- What?
- Marnie! No, Marnie!

34:40.120 --> 34:41.621
- Oh, my God!
- No, you should have it.

34:41.705 --> 34:45.170
Okay, I know you're not my birth mother,
but will you please be my earth mother?

34:45.250 --> 34:46.963
- No!
- What!

34:47.043 --> 34:49.591
My mom's not dead,
but will you be mine, too?

34:49.670 --> 34:52.174
- And mine, please!
- Mine, too!

34:58.847 --> 35:02.521
Anyway, I just wanted to make sure
you're gonna be back in time

35:02.601 --> 35:05.398
for what's-her-name's wedding. I don't
think you're gonna want to miss it.

35:05.478 --> 35:07.776
For making squished sandwiches with it...

35:07.856 --> 35:10.195
- Oh, paninis.
- Paninis, yeah.

35:10.275 --> 35:13.028
It's gonna be the party of the century.

35:13.111 --> 35:16.451
So hopefully, you don't have to do
re-shoots or whatever.

35:16.531 --> 35:18.533
Anyway, I hope you're having fun.

35:18.617 --> 35:21.211
I'm kind of dying
to find out how it's going.

35:22.078 --> 35:25.252
I miss you, but, basically, I feel fine.

35:25.332 --> 35:29.678
So, give me a call, but if you can't...

35:32.922 --> 35:34.261
What the hell, lady?

35:34.341 --> 35:36.435
Okay. Love you.

35:43.975 --> 35:47.566
And then I realized that
Freddy didn't have anyone to study with.

35:47.646 --> 35:53.071
So, I found out what classes he was
taking and what books he needed,

35:53.151 --> 35:55.865
and I got them on Amazon, half-price.

35:55.945 --> 35:58.198
So now, I can help him study.

35:59.240 --> 36:01.079
Why do you think you're helping him?

36:01.159 --> 36:04.914
Well, he comes from a poor neighborhood,
his mother works all the time,

36:04.996 --> 36:09.170
and, you know, education is
the most important thing to him.

36:09.250 --> 36:11.628
- And Jillian?
- Jillian?

36:11.711 --> 36:14.759
Well, Jillian, she never had
a proper lesbian wedding.

36:14.839 --> 36:17.512
And... I had the money

36:17.592 --> 36:20.516
and so I thought, "I can do that."

36:21.721 --> 36:22.938
What's Jillian's last name?

36:25.809 --> 36:27.436
Begins with a "G"...

36:28.478 --> 36:29.479
or a "K".

36:29.562 --> 36:31.030
It's a consonant.

36:31.690 --> 36:33.988
- A consonant.
- A consonant.

36:35.318 --> 36:36.319
Marnie?

36:36.403 --> 36:39.075
Do you think there's a part of you

36:39.155 --> 36:41.829
that maybe feels guilty that
you have your husband's money?

36:43.326 --> 36:45.203
Like you've been given
this consolation prize...

36:46.037 --> 36:48.381
you don't know what to do with?

36:49.833 --> 36:51.085
Or maybe there's a part of you...

36:52.669 --> 36:55.923
that feels like maybe money
is the way to save everybody.

36:56.005 --> 37:00.347
Or possibly even a way to stay
in people's lives and be needed?

37:00.427 --> 37:06.184
And that this relationship that you
have with Freddy and Jillian,

37:06.266 --> 37:10.066
it's really all about just replacing
your own husband and daughter?

37:11.604 --> 37:15.528
So I told her,
"I don't need to replace anyone."

37:15.608 --> 37:18.111
And why would I feel guilty
about Joe's money?

37:18.194 --> 37:20.697
I mean, he started out from nothing.
He worked hard all his life.

37:20.780 --> 37:22.994
He would have wanted me
to do something good with it, right?

37:23.074 --> 37:24.496
Like Cinderella.

37:26.453 --> 37:29.167
But she kept asking me all these questions

37:29.247 --> 37:30.999
and saying all this stuff.

37:31.082 --> 37:34.256
And I was like, "You're a therapist.
Aren't you supposed to listen?"

37:36.796 --> 37:38.469
Anyways...

37:40.175 --> 37:43.850
You know, this is one of
the best hospitals in the country.

39:00.296 --> 39:02.635
Look at this! Is this yours?

39:02.715 --> 39:05.555
No. Well, it was my husband's.
So, yeah, I guess it is.

39:05.635 --> 39:07.763
Got room for one more?

39:07.846 --> 39:10.599
Marnie, this is my brother, Fredo.

39:10.682 --> 39:13.811
Yeah. Well, oh, my.

39:13.893 --> 39:15.106
So nice to meet you.

39:15.186 --> 39:18.941
I kinda promised him we'd give him
a ride someplace. Is that cool?

39:19.023 --> 39:21.488
Actually, I have one stop to make first.

39:21.568 --> 39:22.694
Oh, sure, sure.

39:22.777 --> 39:25.155
Any brother of Freddy's
is a friend of mine.

39:25.238 --> 39:26.615
Shotgun!

39:28.199 --> 39:29.871
Hey, does the top come down on this thing?

39:29.951 --> 39:31.372
- Sure.
- Yeah.

39:31.452 --> 39:33.580
See, this the kinda car I want.

39:33.663 --> 39:36.878
Except I'll paint mine black,
you know, like a matte black.

39:36.958 --> 39:38.710
That's an idea.

39:38.793 --> 39:41.382
Hey, you remember that time
Tre stole that car,

39:41.462 --> 39:45.558
but it turned out to be a hearse and you
were so scared you pissed your pants?

39:48.386 --> 39:49.478
He was so scared.

39:55.018 --> 39:57.737
- I'll just be two minutes.
- Sure.

40:03.109 --> 40:05.362
Sorry about this,
but thanks for taking him.

40:05.445 --> 40:07.617
Of course, it's nice to see
the two of you together.

40:07.697 --> 40:09.449
Hey, man.

40:11.075 --> 40:14.705
You know, if you want, we could
stop for ice cream on the way back.

40:25.882 --> 40:28.805
And the difference between a veto
and a pocket veto?

40:28.885 --> 40:34.392
A pocket veto is when the President
doesn't sign a bill for ten days,

40:34.474 --> 40:37.272
but Congress can't overrule it.

40:37.352 --> 40:39.480
Yes! You are ready, Freddy.

40:39.562 --> 40:41.484
Oh. "Ready Freddy." I like that.

40:41.564 --> 40:44.283
That's funny. What's that?

40:46.235 --> 40:48.575
Fredo... He's...

40:48.655 --> 40:50.827
- I'm sorry.
- Is that marijuana?

40:50.907 --> 40:52.328
- It must have fallen...
- What's it doing...

40:52.408 --> 40:55.206
- Oh, my God.
- Okay, okay, what do we do?

40:55.286 --> 40:57.834
- What are we gonna do?
- Sorry, Joey.

40:57.914 --> 41:00.417
What are you doing? What are you...?

41:01.376 --> 41:02.719
Okay...

41:09.133 --> 41:11.306
Are you all right, ma'am?

42:51.527 --> 42:53.366
Can I help you?

42:53.446 --> 42:55.785
How much are the pies?

42:55.865 --> 42:57.742
They're all $12.

42:57.825 --> 43:00.954
I can have all of them for $12?

43:06.751 --> 43:08.923
Hey, I know you.

43:09.003 --> 43:10.880
Nope.

43:10.963 --> 43:13.386
Sure, I do. You're an actress, right?

43:13.466 --> 43:16.305
You're a police officer man.

43:16.385 --> 43:21.266
Yeah, well, retired, technically,
but they still need us on set.

43:21.349 --> 43:23.943
You know, in case a director
starts throwing stuff.

43:25.019 --> 43:27.608
Everybody calls me Zipper.

43:27.688 --> 43:29.861
Okay.

43:29.941 --> 43:33.239
And you are Miss...?

43:33.319 --> 43:34.946
Minervini.

43:35.029 --> 43:36.406
Miss Minervini.

43:36.489 --> 43:39.493
Mrs. Minervini.

43:39.575 --> 43:40.663
Missus.

43:40.743 --> 43:42.540
Well, actually,
I don't know if it's still missus

43:42.620 --> 43:45.668
- because my husband died, and I...
- I'm sorry.

43:45.748 --> 43:47.211
Thank you.

43:47.291 --> 43:51.758
It goes back to maybe
the maiden name, or...

43:51.838 --> 43:54.341
'Cause when you're divorced
I don't think that you still...

43:54.423 --> 43:57.221
I mean, that's... Of course that's
different, but I think maybe...

43:57.301 --> 43:58.302
Just... It would be...

43:59.846 --> 44:02.190
less confusing if you call me...

44:03.558 --> 44:04.901
Marnie.

44:06.185 --> 44:07.732
Okay, Marnie.

44:09.272 --> 44:12.236
Well, Marnie, do you wanna join us?

44:12.316 --> 44:13.613
Us?

44:13.693 --> 44:15.946
In a different language. Portuguese.

44:19.031 --> 44:22.580
So, we get to the area and, sure enough,

44:22.660 --> 44:24.332
there is this naked guy,

44:24.412 --> 44:26.380
and he's just walking up the street...

44:32.420 --> 44:35.173
refuses to put on clothes
or get in the car,

44:35.256 --> 44:37.384
and Bernie suggests that we...

44:41.637 --> 44:43.014
He would not go down!

44:43.097 --> 44:44.519
He just stands there, vibrating!

44:44.599 --> 44:46.476
Just pointing north!

44:47.977 --> 44:50.525
Oh, pardon my language.

44:50.605 --> 44:52.482
Were you talking?

44:57.153 --> 44:58.575
Thank you.

45:01.574 --> 45:03.576
Sorry about that. Those...

45:03.659 --> 45:07.959
Those guys are... They're good guys, but
they do like hearing themselves talk.

45:08.039 --> 45:10.883
Well, if I had those stories,
I would listen to myself think.

45:14.003 --> 45:15.676
Well...

45:18.799 --> 45:20.596
I gotta get going.

45:20.676 --> 45:23.975
I have to, dog-sit my daughter's kids,

45:24.055 --> 45:27.559
and, you know, my hands are... loud.

45:29.435 --> 45:30.482
Okay.

45:31.896 --> 45:35.776
Do you maybe need a ride or...

45:35.858 --> 45:38.030
No, I can't drive that.

45:38.110 --> 45:40.199
Okay.

45:40.279 --> 45:44.159
How about just this once I drive it,
and you can sit on the back?

45:44.242 --> 45:48.040
That's crazy. I would kill my daughter
if she died on a motorcycle.

45:48.120 --> 45:49.542
Oh, this isn't a motorcycle.

45:50.831 --> 45:52.708
This is a Harley Davidson.

45:53.459 --> 45:55.302
It's a world of difference.

45:56.212 --> 45:57.259
Come on, it'll be fun.

45:58.089 --> 46:00.511
The safest place you can be in Los Angeles

46:00.591 --> 46:03.891
is on this seat right here. I promise.

46:04.720 --> 46:06.393
I'll go slow.

46:12.728 --> 46:14.442
So tell me about your daughter.

46:14.522 --> 46:16.490
Not now!

46:22.071 --> 46:24.118
So why do they call you Zipper?

46:24.198 --> 46:26.245
It's my name.

46:26.325 --> 46:28.122
My last name.

46:28.202 --> 46:30.124
Then... that makes sense.

46:30.204 --> 46:31.918
- Yeah.
- What's your first name?

46:31.998 --> 46:33.711
Randy.

46:33.791 --> 46:35.668
- Or Randall.
- Randall.

46:35.751 --> 46:37.628
And are you from around here?

46:37.712 --> 46:39.383
Am I asking too many questions?

46:39.463 --> 46:41.181
No.

46:42.216 --> 46:45.139
I'm from outside Oxnard originally.

46:45.219 --> 46:47.722
And then I moved to Ventura
when I got married,

46:47.805 --> 46:51.059
and moved to Topanga when I got divorced.

46:51.142 --> 46:52.230
Oh, I'm sorry.

46:52.310 --> 46:55.530
Oh, don't be sorry. She's not.

46:57.565 --> 47:00.444
You know, she never smiled with her teeth.

47:00.526 --> 47:02.199
I should've known.

47:04.572 --> 47:06.574
Is Topanga on the beach?

47:06.657 --> 47:09.285
No, not on the beach, by the beach.

47:11.245 --> 47:12.872
I wouldn't mind living on the beach.

47:12.955 --> 47:14.457
Yeah.

47:15.333 --> 47:17.586
But I don't know
where I'd keep the chickens.

47:18.961 --> 47:20.178
Chickens?

47:21.547 --> 47:24.512
Yeah. Yeah. You got your dog people
and your cat people.

47:24.592 --> 47:27.181
I am a man with chickens.

47:27.261 --> 47:28.683
Get outta here.

47:28.763 --> 47:29.809
No...

47:29.889 --> 47:31.641
- Chickens?
- Absolutely.

47:32.933 --> 47:33.934
How many?

47:34.018 --> 47:36.396
Well, you know what they say
about counting chickens?

47:36.479 --> 47:37.981
No.

47:38.064 --> 47:41.443
You don't know what they say
about counting chickens, really?

47:41.525 --> 47:42.777
No.

47:42.860 --> 47:44.448
Didn't your grandma ever tell you that?

47:44.528 --> 47:47.156
No, we didn't...
My grandma didn't have chickens.

47:47.239 --> 47:49.787
Oh, yeah. You are a city girl, aren't you?

47:49.867 --> 47:53.207
Well, my chickens and I have a very
symbiotic relationship.

47:53.287 --> 47:55.835
I give them a coop and some feed,

47:55.915 --> 47:58.629
once in a while,
a little Parmesan cheese for a treat,

47:58.709 --> 48:00.803
and they keep me in eggs.

48:03.130 --> 48:04.632
Matter of fact... Excuse me.

48:08.094 --> 48:10.516
Oh, I can't believe it didn't break.

48:10.596 --> 48:13.520
Yeah. That's from the Ameraucana.
She's my only Easter egger.

48:17.603 --> 48:18.775
You wanna meet her?

48:19.980 --> 48:21.106
At your house?

48:21.190 --> 48:23.863
Well, she's been out at the bar
most of the night,

48:23.943 --> 48:26.162
but she's probably home by now.

48:33.661 --> 48:35.207
Watch your step there.

48:35.287 --> 48:39.918
Here, let me go in first.
Make sure we don't let anybody escape.

48:43.170 --> 48:47.300
Well, now here's...
That's Patsy, and Kathleen.

48:47.383 --> 48:49.805
Over here is, that's Ayla.

48:49.885 --> 48:52.850
Katie and Ruth. That's Gayle.

48:52.930 --> 48:56.771
And... the golden girl there is Henrietta.

48:56.851 --> 48:59.190
And now don't let her sass you.

48:59.270 --> 49:02.568
She gets a little attitude
on account of she's so damn beautiful.

49:02.648 --> 49:03.986
So beautiful.

49:04.066 --> 49:05.784
Girls, this is Marnie.

49:06.652 --> 49:08.654
Hey.

49:09.697 --> 49:11.369
Was out here a couple months ago

49:11.449 --> 49:14.997
and I brought that boombox with me
and I was playing some tunes.

49:15.077 --> 49:18.542
And I looked at their faces,
and I swear they just looked happy.

49:18.622 --> 49:20.169
So I did a little experiment

49:20.249 --> 49:23.002
to try and find out what kind of music
they dig the most.

49:23.294 --> 49:26.008
Turns out, rock 'n' roll makes
'em lay eggs like crazy,

49:26.088 --> 49:28.135
but it does stress 'em out a little bit.

49:28.215 --> 49:30.012
Oh, I understand.

49:30.092 --> 49:31.890
Classical's good. They like that.

49:33.053 --> 49:35.101
- Reggae, not good.
- Really?

49:35.181 --> 49:37.149
No. Don't know what it is.

49:37.641 --> 49:42.397
Turns out, for the optimal combination
of happiness and productivity...

49:43.439 --> 49:45.658
all roads lead to Dolly.

50:03.000 --> 50:05.503
How can you tell if it's working?

50:07.171 --> 50:09.594
Don't they look like they're smiling?

50:12.468 --> 50:13.970
Yeah, they do.

50:30.861 --> 50:34.285
Joey didn't want to know how much time
he had left, but Lori and I knew.

50:34.365 --> 50:39.838
And he asked her to throw us
a wedding anniversary party in August.

50:40.663 --> 50:43.878
But... she knew he
wouldn't be around that long,

50:43.958 --> 50:47.053
so she said, which was so brilliant...

50:47.836 --> 50:51.716
"Why don't I throw you a
'40 Years From The Day You Met' party?"

50:52.341 --> 50:55.639
And she decorated
the whole house like 1969.

50:55.719 --> 50:58.142
And the music was 1969,

50:58.222 --> 51:00.850
and all her friends
came dressed like the '60s.

51:01.392 --> 51:05.568
And his brothers flew out,
and we had fondue.

51:06.355 --> 51:08.824
It was a spectacular day.

51:09.942 --> 51:11.285
What about you?

51:11.902 --> 51:13.279
You got kids?

51:13.362 --> 51:14.614
Two beautiful girls.

51:15.531 --> 51:16.827
- Nice.
- Yeah.

51:16.907 --> 51:19.205
The one that likes me
lives halfway across the country,

51:19.285 --> 51:21.754
and the one that doesn't
is just over in Palm Springs.

51:22.329 --> 51:23.455
Of course.

51:24.123 --> 51:25.466
Lizzie was...

51:26.000 --> 51:28.839
She was still in high school
when her mom and I fell apart,

51:28.919 --> 51:31.138
which was my fault, mostly.

51:31.922 --> 51:33.174
Seventy-thirty.

51:35.050 --> 51:36.677
Sixty-forty maybe.

51:37.886 --> 51:40.435
I was working all the time, you know.

51:41.640 --> 51:43.642
And then I brought it home with me.

51:43.726 --> 51:48.527
And then, when she started to slip away,
I was just gripping and...

51:51.984 --> 51:54.448
She's in a reha... in a program now.

51:54.528 --> 51:55.996
She's in a program.

51:57.990 --> 52:01.961
Kept hoping one of those steps
would lead her back here, but...

52:03.329 --> 52:07.004
I think I just made her
scared to tell me things.

52:07.958 --> 52:11.173
Sure, what...
Look what you were seeing every day,

52:11.253 --> 52:13.592
all that serial killers and stuff.

52:13.672 --> 52:16.845
I mean, I watch the news,
never mind being part of it,

52:16.925 --> 52:20.015
it's like being in an action movie
or something.

52:20.095 --> 52:21.312
Yeah, well...

52:23.515 --> 52:24.562
not anymore.

52:24.642 --> 52:27.316
It's not your fault
the world's a scary place.

52:28.354 --> 52:29.822
Thank God you're retired.

52:30.898 --> 52:33.117
Yep. Yeah, it has its moments.

52:33.942 --> 52:35.694
And I have learned to calm down.

52:37.112 --> 52:38.455
You know, I mean, if...

52:39.448 --> 52:41.325
Lizzie doesn't want me
to call her anymore,

52:41.408 --> 52:42.871
I have to respect that.

52:42.951 --> 52:45.170
No. You don't... I mean...

52:46.455 --> 52:48.002
You can't not call.

52:48.624 --> 52:50.217
Well, I mean, I...

52:50.668 --> 52:52.881
I left messages until it was full.

52:52.961 --> 52:54.049
So?

52:54.129 --> 52:55.301
Sorry.

52:56.382 --> 52:59.727
I mean, it's not my business,
but you have to call her.

53:00.511 --> 53:02.309
Well, I...

53:03.263 --> 53:05.641
I really wouldn't know what to say.

53:05.724 --> 53:08.273
You just tell her that you love her
no matter what she's up to.

53:09.144 --> 53:12.523
You know, everybody knows their mother
loves them unconditionally,

53:12.606 --> 53:14.734
but fathers have to
say it out loud, I think.

53:23.242 --> 53:24.915
What time is it?

53:46.306 --> 53:47.558
Here you go, I'll trade you.

53:47.641 --> 53:48.813
Thanks.

53:50.894 --> 53:52.362
Take that, too.

53:54.106 --> 53:55.278
Thank you.

53:57.985 --> 53:59.737
Hang on here, let me...

54:00.404 --> 54:01.621
Let me give you this.

54:02.573 --> 54:06.203
You know, in case you need to get
out of a speeding ticket or something.

54:07.995 --> 54:09.212
Cool.

54:15.878 --> 54:17.050
Here, doggies.

56:02.317 --> 56:06.447
Anyway, I'm landing at JFK at 5:30.

56:06.530 --> 56:08.702
Just thought I should head
back east for a little bit,

56:08.782 --> 56:11.752
see Daddy's brothers and maybe
get to visit you on the set.

56:13.871 --> 56:15.248
Don't worry about the dogs.

56:15.330 --> 56:18.630
I dropped them off at Jacob's house
so they'd be somewhere familiar.

56:20.836 --> 56:23.760
To be honest, I can't wait
to be back in the city.

56:25.382 --> 56:27.680
Seeing the old stomping grounds...

56:28.802 --> 56:31.851
walking through Midtown
in the Garment District...

56:33.056 --> 56:34.808
and seeing Daddy's old building.

56:39.271 --> 56:41.273
But mostly, I can't wait to see you.

56:42.024 --> 56:44.368
So, let me know when's a good time.

56:48.363 --> 56:50.741
We skip that, because that's,
like, the whole point.

56:50.824 --> 56:52.621
That's like the only real thing.
Know what I mean?

56:52.701 --> 56:55.123
It just feels like none of these things
my character would say.

56:55.203 --> 56:57.042
Is there any way
we can get some new pages?

56:57.122 --> 56:59.625
- What would you like to say?
- Just something less jokey.

56:59.708 --> 57:01.176
Hi!

57:02.294 --> 57:03.796
- Hi.
- Nice to meet you.

57:03.879 --> 57:04.925
- Hi.
- Hi.

57:05.005 --> 57:07.224
- Thanks.
- I'm gonna find you and...

57:08.175 --> 57:09.972
- Hi. Hi, Mom.
- Hi, sweetie.

57:10.052 --> 57:11.804
This is your chair, okay?

57:13.513 --> 57:14.810
And, then...

57:15.390 --> 57:17.518
This... These are your headphones.

57:17.601 --> 57:20.901
Okay? And... don't talk to anybody.

57:21.355 --> 57:23.652
Just... And the safe word is "Cantaloupe."

57:23.732 --> 57:24.903
- Okay.
- Okay?

57:24.983 --> 57:25.984
Okay.

57:30.489 --> 57:31.866
On the bell.

57:37.162 --> 57:38.750
And, action.

57:38.830 --> 57:40.457
All right. Call me, okay?

57:40.540 --> 57:41.757
Good night.

57:44.086 --> 57:46.464
Jesus! Mom, you scared the crap out of me!

57:46.546 --> 57:49.136
Come on, don't you have ice-cream
in the guest house?

57:49.216 --> 57:52.431
Well, yeah, but I already picked all
the cookie dough out of it.

57:52.511 --> 57:53.808
What are you reading?

57:54.471 --> 57:56.685
- Is that my journal?
- Is that what this is?

57:56.765 --> 57:58.642
I thought the character
was a little slutty.

57:58.725 --> 57:59.897
Give me that.

57:59.977 --> 58:02.105
Aren't you too old to keep a journal?

58:02.187 --> 58:04.276
Aren't you too old to be reading
your daughter's journal?

58:04.356 --> 58:07.075
That's a violation of space and time!

58:07.609 --> 58:09.698
Now, what's all the yelling about?

58:09.778 --> 58:11.530
I violated space and time.

58:12.990 --> 58:16.540
So, what, you... you peed
in the upstairs, shower, too, huh?

58:17.285 --> 58:19.413
What's wrong with the shower
in the guest house?

58:19.496 --> 58:23.217
Well, it's got this, weird smell.

58:25.168 --> 58:29.217
Mom, Dad, when I said you
should move here after you retire,

58:29.297 --> 58:31.845
I didn't mean "here," here.
Okay? I need to get a life.

58:31.925 --> 58:34.724
I need to meet a guy and get married,
so I can give you grandchildren, so...

58:35.721 --> 58:37.064
Wet towel, Dad.

58:48.775 --> 58:49.947
Cut!

58:51.945 --> 58:54.289
Here, and jump straight to there.

58:55.615 --> 58:57.913
I just feel like
we could land it a little better.

58:57.993 --> 59:00.997
- And we need another option for that.
- All right.

59:01.079 --> 59:02.797
I think, definitely, write that down.

59:05.500 --> 59:07.753
Hey, you. That was so good.

59:08.336 --> 59:10.425
Not too big? Did you love it?

59:10.505 --> 59:11.843
- Perfect.
- Space and time...

59:11.923 --> 59:14.346
- Great, great, great, great.
- Awesome, man. Thanks.

59:26.438 --> 59:28.861
You look so much like him.

59:30.108 --> 59:31.360
I'm sorry?

59:32.235 --> 59:36.741
The... character that
you're playing, it, it's...

59:37.157 --> 59:40.957
You look so much like
the man that it's based on.

59:41.953 --> 59:44.251
I didn't realize it was,
you know, based on...

59:44.331 --> 59:46.254
- So much like...
- Cantaloupe!

59:49.002 --> 59:50.465
Would you like some cantaloupe,

59:50.545 --> 59:53.173
because we have a fresh tray going around.

59:53.256 --> 59:56.135
And then that's when,
that's when he looks down

59:56.218 --> 59:58.181
- and sees this giant snake right there.
- No, no, no!

59:58.261 --> 59:59.638
And he's like... he's like,

59:59.721 --> 01:00:02.269
"Jock! What's this
huge snake in the plane?!"

01:00:02.349 --> 01:00:04.602
And, and Jock's like,
"Oh, that's just Reggie."

01:00:04.684 --> 01:00:07.024
And, and Indy's like, "I hate snakes!"

01:00:07.104 --> 01:00:09.448
And then they just fly off
into the sunset.

01:00:10.023 --> 01:00:11.945
Yeah. And that's the first 20 minutes

01:00:12.025 --> 01:00:14.278
of Indiana Jones
and the Raiders of the Lost Ark.

01:00:14.361 --> 01:00:15.824
Yeah. Yeah. Thank you.

01:00:15.904 --> 01:00:17.576
- I never saw it.
- What?

01:00:17.656 --> 01:00:19.995
No. I feel like I've seen it now,
but I never saw it.

01:00:20.075 --> 01:00:22.077
Well, we gotta watch it
before you leave town.

01:00:22.160 --> 01:00:23.331
- All right.
- Movie night.

01:00:23.411 --> 01:00:24.663
- I like it.
- Thank you.

01:00:25.872 --> 01:00:27.461
Drink it, drink it, drink it,
drink it, drink it...

01:00:27.541 --> 01:00:29.134
You two meet on the set?

01:00:30.418 --> 01:00:32.546
Yeah, just two weeks ago.

01:00:32.629 --> 01:00:34.973
Like I was telling you,
right before you asked him to dinner.

01:00:35.715 --> 01:00:38.555
I think it is so romantic,
meeting on a movie set.

01:00:38.635 --> 01:00:41.263
Well, not really, I mean, plenty
of people meet on movie sets.

01:00:41.346 --> 01:00:43.060
It's usually scandalous and home-wrecking.

01:00:43.140 --> 01:00:44.478
That's so true. So true.

01:00:44.558 --> 01:00:46.396
I met Lori's father in Atlantic City.

01:00:46.476 --> 01:00:48.069
It was pretty romantic.

01:00:48.603 --> 01:00:50.230
And then we got married six months later.

01:00:50.313 --> 01:00:51.359
Six months?

01:00:51.439 --> 01:00:52.652
Yeah. I think when you know, you know.

01:00:52.732 --> 01:00:54.530
I totally agree with you,
you know something...

01:00:56.862 --> 01:00:58.575
You know, I'm just gonna
run to the bathroom.

01:00:58.655 --> 01:01:00.077
Tinkle time.

01:01:01.366 --> 01:01:03.835
Okay, hurry back. Dinner's coming.

01:01:05.954 --> 01:01:07.422
Yeah, there we go.

01:01:09.040 --> 01:01:10.504
She's so lovely.

01:01:10.584 --> 01:01:12.211
- Good job.
- She is lovely. Thank you.

01:01:12.294 --> 01:01:14.171
Yeah. So, hey...

01:01:18.341 --> 01:01:21.139
Oh, my God.

01:01:21.219 --> 01:01:22.971
I got that the day after we met.

01:01:23.805 --> 01:01:26.183
You know, when I know
I want something, I go get it.

01:01:26.266 --> 01:01:27.859
That's how I got this far in my career.

01:01:28.435 --> 01:01:31.564
Russell Boyd, Rodney Charters,
Don McAlpine.

01:01:31.646 --> 01:01:34.611
When the top cinematographers
need a B camera operator,

01:01:34.691 --> 01:01:36.279
do you know who they call?

01:01:36.359 --> 01:01:39.408
- You?
- Boom! When you know you know!

01:01:42.616 --> 01:01:44.664
- Yeah.
- It's so fast.

01:01:46.119 --> 01:01:47.746
But, if Lori's happy...

01:01:47.829 --> 01:01:50.457
I was thinking we'd get everyone
she knows together,

01:01:50.540 --> 01:01:54.506
and we, we put together
one of those YouTube videos.

01:01:54.586 --> 01:01:56.633
And everyone she knows
comes out one by one,

01:01:56.713 --> 01:01:58.885
doing a choreographed dance number.

01:01:58.965 --> 01:02:01.179
And then it ends with me
appearing with the ring...

01:02:01.259 --> 01:02:04.763
This will all be
one tracking shot, of course.

01:02:04.846 --> 01:02:07.144
I love it. Oh, my gosh.
That's so beautiful.

01:02:07.224 --> 01:02:10.353
- I'm gonna propose to her...
- She's gonna love it.

01:02:10.435 --> 01:02:12.563
I just feel like the whole thing

01:02:12.646 --> 01:02:17.195
is getting bastardized
by everybody's notes, you know?

01:02:17.275 --> 01:02:20.449
By now, I can't even remember what
I was trying to say in the first place.

01:02:22.489 --> 01:02:23.785
Why are you so hyper?

01:02:23.865 --> 01:02:25.492
I'm not. I'm just excited for you.

01:02:26.159 --> 01:02:29.124
And... Ben seems nice.

01:02:29.204 --> 01:02:31.332
Yeah, well, do not get used to him, Mom,

01:02:31.414 --> 01:02:33.461
because that's not gonna last.

01:02:33.541 --> 01:02:35.338
I'm not so sure.

01:02:35.418 --> 01:02:38.633
No, I'm telling you, I'm just rebounding.

01:02:38.713 --> 01:02:42.053
But, you know, sometimes people think
that they're having a rebound

01:02:42.133 --> 01:02:44.261
and then it evolves into something more.

01:02:46.054 --> 01:02:48.852
Actually, there's something
I have to tell you.

01:02:48.932 --> 01:02:50.400
Come here.

01:02:55.605 --> 01:02:57.733
I was engaged to someone else
before Daddy.

01:02:58.316 --> 01:03:00.034
Yeah, you told me that before.

01:03:00.485 --> 01:03:01.573
I did?

01:03:01.653 --> 01:03:04.868
Yeah, his name was Matteo
and you weren't that attracted to him,

01:03:04.948 --> 01:03:06.912
then you went to Atlantic City
with your girlfriends,

01:03:06.992 --> 01:03:08.244
and that's where you met Daddy.

01:03:08.326 --> 01:03:10.078
You have, like, three stories, Mom.

01:03:10.161 --> 01:03:12.584
All right, all right,
so you're rebounding.

01:03:12.664 --> 01:03:15.213
Well, then, why don't you
and Jacob give it another go?

01:03:18.545 --> 01:03:20.968
Because that's not up to me.

01:03:21.756 --> 01:03:24.930
Well... maybe if you tell him
how you feel.

01:03:25.468 --> 01:03:27.933
See that's the great lie
of your life, Mom.

01:03:28.013 --> 01:03:29.765
You think if you dream it, you can do it.

01:03:29.848 --> 01:03:32.226
- The world just doesn't work that way.
- What are you talking about?

01:03:32.309 --> 01:03:35.148
You dreamt that you would be a writer,
and you did it.

01:03:35.228 --> 01:03:37.525
You dreamt you would come
to Hollywood, and you did it.

01:03:37.605 --> 01:03:40.108
You dream up lots of stories,
all the time.

01:03:41.776 --> 01:03:44.741
That reminds me, I met the cutest girl
in the bathroom at JFK.

01:03:44.821 --> 01:03:47.410
She's in a wheelchair and she's a blogger.

01:03:47.490 --> 01:03:49.117
She empowers young women.

01:03:49.200 --> 01:03:50.747
And, I told her you were a writer.

01:03:50.827 --> 01:03:53.250
She didn't know who you were,
but she was very, very excited

01:03:53.330 --> 01:03:54.501
about the possibility...

01:03:54.581 --> 01:03:58.004
I told her you would have coffee with
her and give her some industry tips.

01:03:58.084 --> 01:04:00.048
I don't have any industry tips.

01:04:00.128 --> 01:04:01.505
Well, it's just coffee.

01:04:02.255 --> 01:04:03.723
She's in a wheelchair.

01:04:23.068 --> 01:04:25.412
How do you take a selfie?

01:04:25.528 --> 01:04:28.247
What do you mean?
You just take a picture of yourself.

01:04:28.865 --> 01:04:31.459
Yeah, but, how do you
take a picture of yourself?

01:04:32.035 --> 01:04:34.037
Who are you sending a selfie to?

01:04:37.540 --> 01:04:38.712
Just never mind.

01:04:38.792 --> 01:04:41.006
- Never mind.
- Do you have a new friend?

01:04:41.086 --> 01:04:42.429
My... I'm not talking about it.

01:04:44.130 --> 01:04:45.882
- I'm not talking about it.
- Mom!

01:04:45.965 --> 01:04:48.263
- Stop.
- Who's your new friend?

01:04:48.343 --> 01:04:50.095
I'm not talking about it. It's not funny.

01:04:50.178 --> 01:04:51.474
- I'm not talking about...
- Can I meet him?

01:04:51.554 --> 01:04:53.768
- Where are the bottles? They in here?
- Did you meet him at The Grove?

01:04:53.848 --> 01:04:55.065
Stop it.

01:04:55.642 --> 01:04:56.643
Stop it.

01:05:00.814 --> 01:05:02.191
This is obviously me.

01:05:03.191 --> 01:05:04.443
Hi, Zipper.

01:05:04.526 --> 01:05:07.450
It's, Marnie Minervini.

01:05:08.279 --> 01:05:10.156
I'm calling from New York,
with my daughter.

01:05:10.240 --> 01:05:11.661
She's doing her TV show.

01:05:11.741 --> 01:05:15.832
And... today I saw the set
and it made me think of you.

01:05:15.912 --> 01:05:18.290
I mean, 'cause of your job.

01:05:18.373 --> 01:05:20.467
Also, I mean, what you do for a living.

01:05:21.584 --> 01:05:25.675
Anyway, so, I ordered some scrambled
eggs at the hotel this morning

01:05:25.755 --> 01:05:27.974
and they were nothing like
what I had of yours.

01:05:29.050 --> 01:05:30.889
I mean, the eggs that you gave me.

01:05:30.969 --> 01:05:32.141
I had one.

01:05:33.221 --> 01:05:34.347
Briefly.

01:05:35.473 --> 01:05:38.021
And so I just thought I would...

01:05:38.101 --> 01:05:40.445
check in on the chickens.

01:05:42.147 --> 01:05:45.362
Also... Oh, yes, my daughter
has a new boyfriend.

01:05:45.442 --> 01:05:47.570
Or should I say fiancÃ©?

01:05:47.652 --> 01:05:49.575
Yep. So, okay.

01:05:50.613 --> 01:05:53.617
So, call me. Okay, love you... Bye!

01:05:54.868 --> 01:05:56.040
Bye.

01:05:59.456 --> 01:06:00.582
- Marnie!
- Marnie!

01:06:08.214 --> 01:06:10.467
- You look very good. California.
- You look very good, very well.

01:06:15.263 --> 01:06:17.311
So, Tina, Tina, how are you feeling?

01:06:20.393 --> 01:06:21.564
How's the TV show?

01:06:21.644 --> 01:06:23.608
So funny. You would not believe.

01:06:23.688 --> 01:06:25.816
I don't know where
she gets her characters from.

01:06:26.649 --> 01:06:28.026
She's a very smart girl.

01:06:28.109 --> 01:06:29.948
- Good imagination more than anything.
- That is mine.

01:06:30.028 --> 01:06:31.575
Salute.

01:06:42.123 --> 01:06:43.375
Very sweet grapes.

01:06:43.458 --> 01:06:45.380
You don't... You don't remember?

01:06:45.460 --> 01:06:46.506
No.

01:06:46.586 --> 01:06:47.963
Two years younger than me.
You don't remember?

01:06:48.046 --> 01:06:49.467
I remember the grub.

01:06:49.547 --> 01:06:50.799
- Yeah.
- That smells good.

01:06:50.882 --> 01:06:54.728
So, the first time I cooked for Joe,
I wanted to make pasta.

01:06:55.678 --> 01:06:58.306
And my mother told me
that the way you know if pasta's done

01:06:58.389 --> 01:07:01.643
- is you throw it against the wall...
- Oh, no.

01:07:01.726 --> 01:07:04.821
...and if it sticks,
then you take it out of the water.

01:07:05.939 --> 01:07:07.532
So I boiled the water.

01:07:08.233 --> 01:07:09.735
I break the pasta in half...

01:07:12.779 --> 01:07:14.326
I know. I know.

01:07:14.781 --> 01:07:16.453
And I start cooking it.

01:07:16.533 --> 01:07:20.208
And... and then I...
throw it against the wall.

01:07:21.454 --> 01:07:22.922
Nothing. Nothing.

01:07:24.123 --> 01:07:27.213
So then I cook it a little bit more,
cook it a little bit more.

01:07:27.293 --> 01:07:31.014
And then finally, I throw it against the
wall and it stuck to the wall.

01:07:31.464 --> 01:07:34.387
And it stuck to itself.
And it stuck to the pot.

01:07:34.467 --> 01:07:36.686
And it stuck to everything it touched.

01:07:37.929 --> 01:07:41.399
So, Joe takes his first bite.

01:07:41.849 --> 01:07:44.522
So, it seems okay. Takes his first bite.

01:07:44.602 --> 01:07:48.232
And then I see him take a little
bit of the pasta off the plate,

01:07:48.314 --> 01:07:50.528
and he puts it in a napkin.

01:07:50.608 --> 01:07:53.531
And I say to him, "What are you doing?"

01:07:53.611 --> 01:07:57.366
And he says,
"I just gotta show this to my mother."

01:08:06.416 --> 01:08:09.088
Yeah, it was a lucky thing we were. Right?

01:08:09.168 --> 01:08:10.795
I would have had a problem.

01:08:12.797 --> 01:08:14.424
I can't believe...

01:08:14.507 --> 01:08:17.477
I can't believe it's
his anniversary already.

01:08:18.219 --> 01:08:20.596
I know, already a year. Unbelievable.

01:08:21.055 --> 01:08:22.682
You mean two years.

01:08:23.390 --> 01:08:25.689
Yeah. A year from last year.

01:08:27.103 --> 01:08:28.649
Time flies, huh?

01:08:28.729 --> 01:08:30.482
- Time flies.
- Time flies.

01:08:31.649 --> 01:08:33.697
So, Marnie...

01:08:34.319 --> 01:08:36.783
We were thinking that...

01:08:36.863 --> 01:08:40.743
you can keep half of his ashes
with you and Lori in California,

01:08:40.825 --> 01:08:44.040
and, the other half
could be buried in Elizabeth.

01:08:44.120 --> 01:08:46.167
- That way...
- We have some place...

01:08:46.247 --> 01:08:49.170
- Yeah, we all have some place to go.
- Yeah, we'll visit, you know.

01:08:49.250 --> 01:08:50.796
Yeah.

01:08:50.877 --> 01:08:53.675
You know, I really think that
I want to talk to Lori about it,

01:08:53.755 --> 01:08:55.843
'cause she's been very sensitive
about the whole thing.

01:08:55.923 --> 01:08:58.011
We already talked to her
and what did she say?

01:08:58.091 --> 01:09:00.265
- She says it's up to you.
- Up to you.

01:09:01.888 --> 01:09:05.228
Since we're all
on the East Coast, for a change,

01:09:05.308 --> 01:09:07.397
we could at least pick out a headstone.

01:09:07.477 --> 01:09:10.149
Lori said you wanted
to use a quote, maybe.

01:09:10.229 --> 01:09:13.194
- Yeah, something from "My Way."
- It doesn't have to be "My Way."

01:09:13.274 --> 01:09:15.863
- How could it not be "My Way"?
- As long as it's Sinatra.

01:09:15.943 --> 01:09:17.694
Well, of course, it is Sinatra, obviously.

01:09:17.779 --> 01:09:19.997
It should be "My Way."
That was his... It should be...

01:09:21.866 --> 01:09:24.540
Marnie, it is all up to you.

01:09:26.496 --> 01:09:29.419
If you want to bury his ashes here, okay.

01:09:29.499 --> 01:09:32.296
And if you wanted to
just sprinkle a little here,

01:09:32.377 --> 01:09:34.220
sprinkle a little over there, fine.

01:09:36.005 --> 01:09:37.218
Up to you.

01:09:37.298 --> 01:09:38.890
How could it not be "My Way"?

01:09:39.966 --> 01:09:41.430
How could it not be "My Way"?

01:09:41.511 --> 01:09:43.057
- Of course.
- It has to be "My Way"!

01:09:43.136 --> 01:09:45.435
We talking about Joe! Joe did it his way!

01:09:45.515 --> 01:09:48.769
He lived his way! It has to be "My Way"!

01:09:48.850 --> 01:09:52.104
No "Strangers in the Night." "My Way"!

01:09:57.151 --> 01:09:59.073
Joseph Minervini?

01:09:59.153 --> 01:10:00.496
What?

01:10:03.449 --> 01:10:06.794
I...I handed you my husband's license.

01:10:07.912 --> 01:10:09.164
There.

01:10:09.831 --> 01:10:12.084
Marnie Minervini. That makes more sense.

01:10:12.166 --> 01:10:14.380
And where you headed today, Ms. Minervini?

01:10:14.460 --> 01:10:16.258
Los Angeles. I live there now.

01:10:17.422 --> 01:10:18.885
How was your time in New York?

01:10:18.965 --> 01:10:21.218
Great. My daughter shot a pilot.

01:10:29.434 --> 01:10:30.731
No. It's...

01:11:28.743 --> 01:11:32.166
Welcome to Los Angeles,
where the local time is 10:37.

01:11:32.246 --> 01:11:34.499
Please remain in your seat
while we taxi to the gate.

01:11:34.582 --> 01:11:36.960
If your cell phone is within reach,
you may use it now.

01:11:45.134 --> 01:11:47.807
Hey, Marnie, it's your new friend, Zipper,

01:11:47.887 --> 01:11:50.476
or Randy, I guess,
depending on who you ask.

01:11:50.556 --> 01:11:52.058
I just saw that you called.

01:11:52.141 --> 01:11:53.893
Sorry I'm just getting back to you now.

01:11:53.976 --> 01:11:56.899
There's, just terrible reception
in the canyon.

01:11:56.979 --> 01:11:58.568
I could barely hear your message.

01:11:58.648 --> 01:12:02.196
But... just wanted to try you back

01:12:02.276 --> 01:12:04.949
and see how the East Coast
is treating you,

01:12:05.029 --> 01:12:10.455
and, also let you know that the chickens
have expanded their musical library

01:12:10.535 --> 01:12:14.333
to include Peggy Lee now,
as well as, Dolly Parton covers,

01:12:14.413 --> 01:12:18.463
so I guess you've got that
to look forward to,

01:12:18.543 --> 01:12:20.965
if you ever make it back this way. But...

01:12:21.045 --> 01:12:24.299
