I leave no regrets.

01:35:06.492 --> 01:35:10.213
To know I left something to remember,
so they won't forget."

01:35:12.624 --> 01:35:15.173
- That sounds like a good one.
- Yeah.

01:35:17.629 --> 01:35:19.222
Well...

01:35:22.717 --> 01:35:25.515
When you bailed me out, did you do that

01:35:25.595 --> 01:35:27.597
because you're an officer of the law?

01:35:29.390 --> 01:35:32.564
No, that's actually the opposite
of what I usually do.

01:35:34.812 --> 01:35:37.110
I bailed you out as a friend.

01:35:50.119 --> 01:35:52.497
You wanna go to an action movie sometime?

01:35:54.791 --> 01:35:55.963
Definitely.

01:36:48.428 --> 01:36:49.805
Mom, where are you?

01:36:49.887 --> 01:36:51.601
You left in the middle of the night
and I got worried.

01:36:51.681 --> 01:36:54.229
Are you okay?
Can you call me when you get this?

01:36:54.309 --> 01:36:55.561
Love you.

01:36:57.353 --> 01:37:00.151
Hey, it's me. I hope you're not mad at me.

01:37:00.231 --> 01:37:02.359
Maybe just text me
and let me know that you got this.

01:37:02.817 --> 01:37:04.490
Okay, love you.

01:37:06.946 --> 01:37:09.661
Okay, I'm officially worried.
Where are you?

01:37:09.741 --> 01:37:12.244
Call me. This is weird.
This is your daughter.

01:37:15.246 --> 01:37:17.248
Hey, Marnie, it's Jillian.

01:37:17.332 --> 01:37:19.629
I was wondering if you could
watch Tehya for me today.

01:37:19.709 --> 01:37:21.552
Dani and I have a thing at seven.

01:37:22.795 --> 01:37:24.968
You're a lifesaver. Thank you.
Dani, we're leaving.

01:37:26.841 --> 01:37:29.344
- Grandma Marnie's here!
- Here she is. Here's my girl!

01:37:31.471 --> 01:37:35.061
Guess what?
We're gonna get to play all night.

01:37:35.141 --> 01:37:37.855
Bye. She's so sad to leave us.

01:37:37.935 --> 01:37:39.312
- She's distraught.
- Yeah.

01:37:39.395 --> 01:37:42.148
Well, we're matching.
This is like the second time.

01:37:42.231 --> 01:37:46.361
What should we do? How about a story?

01:37:46.444 --> 01:37:48.947
- Okay.
- Yes, would you like that?

01:38:17.225 --> 01:38:18.727
Hey, it's Lori. Leave a message.

01:38:20.645 --> 01:38:23.899
Anyways, I just thought I'd check in
and see what you're up to,

01:38:23.981 --> 01:38:25.695
and how your date went last night,

01:38:25.775 --> 01:38:28.364
or whatever it is you
wanted me to call it.

01:38:28.444 --> 01:38:31.698
I don't know how much longer I'm
going to have cell phone reception,

01:38:31.781 --> 01:38:34.579
'cause I'm going to Topanga
to see my friend with the chickens.

01:38:34.659 --> 01:38:39.039
And then, a Jason Statham movie...
His new movie.

01:38:39.122 --> 01:38:41.419
The one where he plays
the guy who stops time.

01:38:41.499 --> 01:38:42.921
It looks fabulous.

01:38:44.210 --> 01:38:47.339
And then tomorrow, I told Jillian

01:38:47.422 --> 01:38:49.385
that I would babysit for Tehya,

01:38:49.465 --> 01:38:52.344
so I'll be in the neighborhood,
if you want me to bring by bagels,

01:38:52.427 --> 01:38:56.017
or look at whatever you're working on
or whatever, you know.

01:38:56.097 --> 01:38:58.475
Because next weekend,
I think I'm gonna go to the desert.

01:38:58.558 --> 01:39:02.106
I'm thinking... I don't know
if I'll actually stay the night,

01:39:02.186 --> 01:39:06.316
but I'm thinking
I'd maybe like to see the desert.

01:39:06.399 --> 01:39:07.862
I mean, it's right there, right?

01:39:07.942 --> 01:39:09.819
Anyway, call me.

01:39:09.902 --> 01:39:11.279
Love you.

